From 42f427587223d7cef4d136eecfaf4b130e383cf8 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: A4100N LCN port <you@example.org>
Date: Thu, 11 Jun 2026 10:33:55 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 3/3] b43: lcn: make CONFIG_B43_PHY_LCN selectable
 (experimental)

The LCN-PHY support was gated behind "depends on B43 && BROKEN", which
compiles out the whole LCN path: PHY recognition in b43_phy_versioning(),
b43_phyops_lcn allocation, and the ucode24_lcn/ucode25_lcn selection in
b43_request_firmware(). As a result b43 never even attempts to claim a
BCM4313 / load its ucode.

Drop the BROKEN dependency so the option can be enabled for development.
With it set, b43 recognises the LCN PHY (phy_rev <= 1, e.g. BCM4313),
allocates the LCN ops and requests b43/ucode24_lcn.fw (extract it with
b43-fwcutter from the proprietary driver).

This only makes the path reachable; bring-up is still incomplete (PHY
calibration not yet ported) so it is labelled EXPERIMENTAL, not fixed.
Part of the LCN-PHY (BCM4313) bring-up for the A4100N.

Signed-off-by: A4100N LCN port <you@example.org>
---
 drivers/net/wireless/broadcom/b43/Kconfig | 11 +++++++----
 1 file changed, 7 insertions(+), 4 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/net/wireless/broadcom/b43/Kconfig b/drivers/net/wireless/broadcom/b43/Kconfig
index 4559549..f9a8203 100644
--- a/drivers/net/wireless/broadcom/b43/Kconfig
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/broadcom/b43/Kconfig
@@ -141,12 +141,15 @@ config B43_PHY_HT
 	  This PHY type with 3x3:3 MIMO can be found in the BCM4331 PCI chipset.
 
 config B43_PHY_LCN
-	bool "Support for LCN-PHY devices (BROKEN)"
-	depends on B43 && BROKEN
+	bool "Support for LCN-PHY devices (EXPERIMENTAL)"
+	depends on B43
 	help
-	  Support for the LCN-PHY.
+	  Support for the LCN-PHY. Work in progress: BCM4313 (e.g. A4100N)
+	  bring-up under b43 with the proprietary ucode (via b43-fwcutter).
 
-	  Say N, this is BROKEN and crashes driver.
+	  Incomplete: PHY calibration is not yet ported, so this may fail to
+	  reach association and can misbehave. Say N unless you are
+	  developing or testing this support.
 
 config B43_PHY_AC
 	bool "Support for AC-PHY (802.11ac) devices (BROKEN)"
